# Tax Accountant Office Website Wireframe - Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Create a high-fidelity wireframe (HTML/CSS) for the top page of a tax accountant office (税理士事務所) website. The goal is to provide a visual structure that can be easily iterated upon and eventually turned into a production site.

## User Review Required
- **Design Preferences**: Need to confirm preferred color scheme (e.g., trustworthy blue, professional navy, warm beige) and target audience (corporate vs. individual inheritance).
- **Key Sections**: Confirmation of proposed sections (Hero, News, Services, Strengths, Staff, Access, Contact).

## Proposed Changes

### Structure
The wireframe will consist of a single `index.html` and a `style.css` file.

#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///C:/Users/hangy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/tax_office_wireframe/index.html)
- **Header**: Logo, Navigation, Phone Number, "Contact Us" button.
- **Hero Section**: Professional background image/color, Catchphrase, Call to Action (CTA).
- **News/Topics**: List of recent updates.
- **Services**: Grid layout showing key services (Corporate Tax, Inheritance, Startups, etc.).
- **Strengths/About Us**: Why choose this firm.
- **Staff/Representative**: Photo and message from the head accountant.
- **Access**: Map placeholder and address.
- **Footer**: Links, Copyright, Contact info.

#### [NEW] [style.css](file:///C:/Users/hangy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/tax_office_wireframe/style.css)
- Basic responsive layout using Flexbox/Grid.
- Clean, professional typography.
- Placeholder colors for visual hierarchy.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- None required for a static wireframe.
### Manual Verification
- Open `index.html` in the browser to verify layout and responsiveness.
- Check that all sections are clearly identifiable.
